The 15 EAP specializing practice takes place in a cultural organization that is connected with students' field of specializing in culture management (music, theater, dance etc). Within at least 8 weeks the students should work in the organization, observe, analyze and take part in organization's everyday work.
As an outcome of the practice there must be a cultural event that the student has been helping to prepare and carry out. The general goal is to put into practice the theoretical knowledge student has gained from curricula so far and use those skills to analyze a cultural organization and its obligations and also use the knowledge in real life practice. Implementing theoretical skills into practice is the key word!
Practice time can take place in one or more organizations depending on the size of the organization and the amount of duties / responsibilities the student has to complete. The amount of a concrete project will be agreed on between the student and practice curator(s).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main goal is to use theoretical skills in actual practice within the area of culture the student is specializing.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1. After passing this course the student has put his or her theoretical knowledge into practice both in analyzing the work plan and character of a cultural organization and also by using learnt theoretical skills in actual organizing process of a cultural event. 2. Student is capable of placing a certain cultural organization in surrounding cultural environment perspective, knows how to analyze the importance, threats and opportunities of the organization in the current situation.  3. Student has mastered general knowledge about the main aspects related to organizing a cultural event: finding your target group, getting funding and making a budget, PR and marketing, event management, reporting and conclusions.
